Electrochemical Engineer

Peroxygen Systems

- Lowell, MA 01852 (Downtown area)

Peroxygen Systems is a clean chemistry company developing an electrolyzer system for producing hydrogen peroxide in a sustainable manner while also lowering cost. Peroxygen is seeking a Technician for employment in its Lowell, MA laboratory. Research staff will train the Technician to build, test, and work with electrochemical systems. The technician role may expand to include supporting installations at customer sites in the future. In joining a start-up company, the Technician will have the opportunity to grow with the company and can develop into a variety of roles
Responsibilities:
Build and test equipment from laboratory scale to commercial scale
Maintain test stands
Perform basic titration experiment
Follow standard operating procedures
Keep detailed records of experiments and testing carried out
Work in a safe manner
Qualifications:
Previous laboratory experience strongly preferred
Hands-on skills working with parts, components, equipment
Physically capable of carrying/moving equipment 50 lbs or more
Ability to repeat experiments with consistent results
Comfortable with chemical/electrical/mechanical systems
Detail oriented and self-motivated with strong communication skills
Job Type: Full-time
